-- Bernanke, Paulson brief Congress on AIG rescue
-- 
-- Tue Sep 16, 2008 7:47pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/16/us-aig-treasury-idUSWBT00971220080916

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson and Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke were briefing members of Congress on the proposed rescue package for American International Group on Tuesday evening, a Treasury official said. 

 The official could not immediately provide any details on the plan. (Reporting by  David Lawder ; Editing by  Gary Hill )